{
  "message": "fix(fnp-conformance): lowercase 23 fixture IDs to satisfy validate_fixture_id policy\n\nvalidate_fixture_id (crates/fnp-conformance/src/test_contracts.rs:296) rejects\nany fixture ID containing uppercase ASCII letters under the current\n`must_be_lowercase` + `allowed_chars = \"a-z0-9_\"` policy. 23 fixture IDs\nacross two JSON files violated this:\n\n- linalg_differential_cases.json (1 ID):\n  linalg_cholesky_solve_identity_L_returns_b\n    \u2192 linalg_cholesky_solve_identity_l_returns_b\n\n- polynomial_differential_cases.json (22 IDs): math-notation polynomial\n  names (Chebyshev T*, Hermite H*, HermiteE He*, Laguerre L*, Legendre P*)\n  lowered to t*/h*/he*/l*/p*. Examples:\n    chebroots_T1_x_has_zero      \u2192 chebroots_t1_x_has_zero\n    hermroots_H2_symmetric_pair  \u2192 hermroots_h2_symmetric_pair\n    hermeroots_He1_linear_has_zero \u2192 hermeroots_he1_linear_has_zero\n    legmul_P0_plus_P1_squared_recurrence \u2192 legmul_p0_plus_p1_squared_recurrence\n\nNo Rust or documentation code referenced these IDs (verified via\n`grep -rn`), so the renames are string-level only. The case-preserving\nmathematical notation is lost, but the policy enforces pure ASCII lower\nidentifiers for replay / audit-trail stability.\n\nOracle output reports auto-regenerated on the subsequent test run to\nreflect the now-admitted case counts:\n  linalg_differential_report.json   67 \u2192 94 cases passed\n  masked_differential_report.json   55 \u2192 78 cases passed\n  polynomial_differential_report.json, rng_differential_report.json,\n  signal_differential_report.json also updated with fresh counts.\n\nTests resolved (this was the umbrella of kuh8's pre-existing\nfixture-id-drift block \u2014 explicitly called out as NOT part of kuh8 but\nnow actionable):\n  fnp-conformance lib test_contracts::tests::test_contract_suite_is_green\n  fnp-conformance lib tests::test_contract_suite_is_green\n  fnp-conformance lib tests::core_suites_are_green\n  fnp-conformance smoke integration core_conformance_suites_pass\n\nVerified via cargo test -p fnp-conformance with CARGO_TARGET_DIR=\n/tmp/rch_target_franken_numpy_cc \u2014 3 lib tests + 1 smoke integration\ntest all ok.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
